# Trivy triage allowlist for the blocking CVE scan (.github/workflows/ci.yml,
# job `cve-scan`). Every entry below is a HIGH/CRITICAL finding from the
# fs scan of api/requirements.txt that was triaged on 2026-07-20 and accepted
# as non-blocking for now.
#
# Do NOT add an entry here without:
#   1. A one-line justification (why it's accepted / not currently exploitable
#      in Citadel's deployment, or the remediation is already scheduled).
#   2. A review-by date (`exp:YYYY-MM-DD`) no more than 90 days out. When the
#      date passes, Trivy stops ignoring the CVE and the job goes red until
#      someone re-triages it (bump the fix, or re-justify + extend the date).
#   3. A link to the tracking issue if the upgrade needs code changes.
#
# See SECURITY.md ("CVE triage process") for the full procedure.

# --- api/requirements.txt --------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-32597 (PyJWT 2.8.0 -> 2.12.0, HIGH): algorithm-confusion issue in
# PyJWT's decode path. Citadel always calls jwt.decode() with an explicit
# `algorithms=["HS256"]` allowlist (api/auth), so the vulnerable code path
# (implicit algorithm inference) is not reachable. Upgrade tracked; blocked on
# passlib/bcrypt pin compatibility check.
CVE-2026-32597 exp:2026-10-18

# CVE-2026-48526 (PyJWT 2.8.0 -> 2.13.0, HIGH): same PyJWT dependency as above;
# batching the upgrade with CVE-2026-32597 rather than bumping twice.
CVE-2026-48526 exp:2026-10-18

# CVE-2024-33663 (python-jose 3.3.0 -> 3.4.0, CRITICAL): algorithm-confusion /
# JWK forgery in python-jose. python-jose is only used for RS256 verification
# against externally-issued license tokens (see api/auth); Citadel's own
# session tokens use PyJWT with a fixed HS256 algorithm, not python-jose.
# Still scheduling the 3.4.0 bump; short expiry to re-check impact.
CVE-2024-33663 exp:2026-08-19

# CVE-2024-53981 (python-multipart 0.0.9 -> 0.0.18, HIGH): DoS via malformed
# multipart boundary parsing (unbounded resource use). Upload endpoints in the
# API sit behind auth + a reverse-proxy body-size limit, which bounds the
# practical impact. Upgrade tracked.
CVE-2024-53981 exp:2026-09-18

# CVE-2026-24486 (python-multipart 0.0.9 -> 0.0.22, HIGH): same package as
# above; batching into the same python-multipart bump.
CVE-2026-24486 exp:2026-09-18

# CVE-2026-42561 (python-multipart 0.0.9 -> 0.0.27, HIGH): same package as
# above; batching into the same python-multipart bump.
CVE-2026-42561 exp:2026-09-18

# CVE-2026-53539 (python-multipart 0.0.9 -> 0.0.30, HIGH): same package as
# above; batching into the same python-multipart bump.
CVE-2026-53539 exp:2026-09-18

# CVE-2025-68616 (weasyprint 62.0 -> 68.0, HIGH): reported in WeasyPrint's SVG/
# CSS handling. WeasyPrint is only invoked server-side against
# internally-generated report templates (PDF export), never on
# user-controlled/untrusted HTML, so the attacker-controlled-input precondition
# is not met in Citadel's usage. Upgrade tracked.
CVE-2025-68616 exp:2026-09-18
